wikipedia.title: Ballistic Missile Early Warning System
wikipedia.summary: The RCA 474L Ballistic Missile Early Warning System (BMEWS, "474L System", Project 474L) was a USAF "Big L" Cold War system of radar, computer, and communications systems that included the first operational ballistic missile detection radar.
